jd: at the time, given how much I was down, I really didn't want to play RYE. the leave doesn't look all that powerful, and I start shutting the board down while leaving conrad a tempo to work with. With two blanks unseen, wherry starts reaching into the bag and keeps things open so I have a better chance of pulling off a comeback.

ultimately, though I think those are things worth worrying about, I'm giving up 10 points a turn extra by not playing RYE. so I need to do it.
>dacrON: ACOOOST 15G OO. +9 216
